column7:
&gt; This is a vast misunderstanding of the American principle of freedom of speech. I can defend your legal freedom to say things but still ostracize you for saying them.  Far too many people think that "freedom of speech" means "freedom from the ramifications of your speech".

No. The point of free speech is to have social norms of free speech, not just to have legal free speech.

&lt;http://slatestarcodex.com/2017/07/29/against-signal-boosting-as-doxxing/&gt;
